Defendant Tydis Trinard Odom in court with attorney Danielle L Shelton.  Defendant Tydis Trinard Odom in custody.  Jennifer L Williams appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Tijuana O. and Carolyn O.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Court sentenced defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONCURRENT to any other sentence with credit for 87 days served.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Court sentenced defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence with credit for 87 days served.

AS TO COUNT 3:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 6 YEARS CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 3 YEARS.  

AS TO COUNT 4:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 3 1/2 YEARS CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 1/2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.  
.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program; is not eligible or the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  
.
CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
1) Obtain AODA assessment and comply with programming; 
2) Maintain absolute sobriety with random urine screens - no illegal drugs; 
3) Obtain full time employment; 
4) Participate in Cognitive Behavioral Therapy Programming; 
5) No contact with Antoinette F. or her family;
6) Participate in Batterer's Intervention Programming;
7) Participate in Sex Offender Treatment;
8) Obtain GED/HSED;
9) Participate in Vocational Programming;
10) Provide a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge as to all 4 counts;
11) Pay all remaining costs and surcharges; if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  Appeal rights given.  Court denied defense request for expungement.

